{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From early childhood on, both my parents and my grandmother stressed to us the importance of menschlichkeit, which in the English language means humaneness.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whenever I wouldn't do something which would measure up to the yardstick of menschlichkeit, they would always used to say, 'Itkele, it's not menschlich.' And that used to helped me more than if they would physically hit me, because I felt like I let them down.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And eventually, I started to measure my own behavior by the yardstick of menschlichkeit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Once, I had an experience, a very painful, actually, experience, which I must-- that was like not too far away before the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because for me, the Holocaust started at age 13, when Germany invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was walking home from school alone, because I had both Hebrew, I mean, Yiddish education and, and went to public school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was walking home from public school, and a bunch of non-Jewish kids-- kids that I didn't even know or didn't know me-- attacked me both verbally and physically.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Called me-- called me terrible names.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I feel-- 'Christ killer' and 'you Jew.' All kinds of names.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Go up to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Go to, you know, very, very insulting names.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I tried to free myself, but the circle closed around me and I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I felt so horrible because I realized, why?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why do they hate me?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How can you hate somebody you don't even know?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I couldn't understand it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I came home crying bitterly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Normally, I didn't cry just for any little thing, so my mother was at that time home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So she asked me, 'Itkele, why are you crying?' And I told her.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Surprisingly, she did not make any comment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She just took me lovingly in her arms and she tried to comfort me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And after a while, when my sobs quiet down, she looked at me seriously, and she asked me, 'So what did you do, my child?' And I was surprised, because I figured, what could I do?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was all alone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I didn't do anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I said, 'Nothing, Mom.' And my mother said reassuringly, 'Well, Itkele, then you have nothing to cry about, because your menschlichkeit does not depend on how others treat you, but on how you treat others.' My parents taught me never to hurt or shame anyone, that that's an [NON-ENGLISH], which means a sin.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But they never, unfortunately, taught me what to do when somebody hurts me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So the only thing I could do when somebody hurt me was crying.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "If-- and-- and everything was measured, like I said, by the yardstick of menschlichkeit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we lived in Poland, physically, our lives were very hard.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For instance, we didn't have-- in our, our hometown, where I lived before the Holocaust, we didn't have electricity in our home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't have running water.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't have plumbing, indoor plumbing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So those things affected very much.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We have to, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But since it was a little city, because of those conditions, for instance, then there was a water carrier, that would bring water to the, you know-- or we would have to fetch water ourselves.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't have electricity.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Therefore, we didn't have any of the modern appliances.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And therefore, we didn't have where to store our food in the summer, it wouldn't get-- so we had a dark root cellar.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They used to call it 'root cellar' because some people would buy for the winter a sack of potatoes and onions, you know, store it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also, you would have to go down for to bring up and down the food.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One time, I remember my mother asked me to go down and bring up the butter from the root cellar, and she saw that I was afraid.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she looked at me and she said, 'Go, go, Itkele.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "God is in the root cellar too.' And she said she'll wait for me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She lit a candle.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She gave me the candle to go down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the root cellar was dark.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It had a dirt floor, no windows, a long ladder.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "To go down-- it was in the kitchen-- you had to-- and an iron ring, it was a square cut out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You would have to pull up the ring, you know, the square, and to walk down.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And somehow, my mother's reassurance, and having the candle, and mostly, she said, 'Go, go.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "God's in the root cellar too.' I don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "For some reason, it gave me the courage.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It diminished my fear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I went down, and I brought up the butter.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
